Build cups4j

* Prerequisites

*---------------------*--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------:
| <<Component>>       | <<Version>>  | <<Comments>>                                                         |
|                     |              |                                                                      |
*---------------------*--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------:
| subversion          |              | To get the sources                                                   |
*---------------------*--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------:
| Java JDK            | 1.7          | To build, do not forget to properly set *JAVA_HOME*                  |
*---------------------*--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------:
| maven 3.x           | 3.*, 3.0.4   | {{{http://maven.apache.org/run-maven/index.html}Properly installed}} |
*---------------------*--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------:
| Internet connection |              | To download dependencies                                             |
*---------------------*--------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------:

* Build
    
    To build cups4j (jar without *and with* dependencies, cups4j.gui tool, javadoc,...) :

+-------------------------------------------
mvn clean
mvn package
mvn install
mvn javadoc:javadoc
+-------------------------------------------

    Once this done (BUILD SUCCESS), you have all proper material
(documentation, javadoc, site) to use cups4j in a comfortable way.

    Documentation, reports, pdf version of the docs are generated in :

+--------------------------------
target/site
+--------------------------------

    To open generated website, just open :

+--------------------------------
target/site/index.html
+--------------------------------

